   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from qiskit import *\n",
    "from qiskit.quantum_info import Pauli\n",
    "from qiskit.primitives import Sampler, Estimator\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization import plot_distribution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1dc1bba3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- `Sampler` takes a quantum circuit or list of circuits (with measurements), and calculates exact quasi-probabilities of bitstrings from quantum circuits by default in ideal conditions.\n",
    "\n",
    "- `Estimator` takes a quantum circuit or list of circuits (without mesasurements), and calculates the exact expectation values of quantum circuits and observables by default in ideal conditions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "b9b7e7d0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def myfunc(my_str):\n",
    "    num_str = len(my_str)\n",
    "    ind = num_str - 1 - np.where(np.array(list(my_str)) == '1')[0]\n",
    "    qc = QuantumCircuit(num_str+1, name ='oracle')\n",
    "    qc.cx(ind, num_str)\n",
    "    U = qc.to_gate()\n",
    "    return U\n",
    "\n",
    "oracle = myfunc('110')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "a32b32a1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sampler = Sampler()\n",
    "estimator = Estimator()"
   ]
  },

    "#### H gate : Hadamard gate, create superposition\n",
    "\n",
    "$H = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} \\begin{bmatrix}1 & 1 \\\\ 1 & -1 \\end{bmatrix} , ~~~~~~  HH = I $\n",
    "\n",
    "$H|0\\rangle = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}(|0\\rangle + |1\\rangle) = |+\\rangle ~~~~~~~~~\n",
    "H|1\\rangle = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}(|0\\rangle - |1\\rangle) = |-\\rangle$ "

    "#### Z gate :  create relative phase $\\pi$\n",
    "\n",
    "$Z = \\begin{bmatrix}1 & 0 \\\\ 0 & -1 \\end{bmatrix} , ~~~~~~ ZZ=I $\n",
    "\n",
    "$Z|0\\rangle = |0\\rangle ~~~~~~~~~\n",
    "Z|1\\rangle = e^{i\\pi} |1\\rangle = - |1\\rangle $ "

   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "angles = np.linspace(0, 8*np.pi, 200)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "id": "c8eef690",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# sending a circuit as one job at a time\n",
    "\n",
    "prob1 = []\n",
    "for ang in angles:\n",
    "    qc = QuantumCircuit(1, 1)\n",
    "    qc.h(0)\n",
    "    qc.p(ang, 0)\n",
    "    qc.h(0)\n",
    "    qc.measure(0, 0)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    prob = sampler.run(qc).result().quasi_dists\n",
    "    if 1 in prob[0]:\n",
    "        prob1.append(prob[0][1])\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        prob1.append(0)"
   ]
  },

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "## sending the list of circuits to a backend as one job\n",
    "\n",
    "qc_all = []\n",
    "for ang in angles:\n",
    "    qc = QuantumCircuit(1, 1)\n",
    "    qc.h(0)\n",
    "    qc.p(ang, 0)\n",
    "    qc.h(0)\n",
    "    qc.measure(0, 0)\n",
    "    qc_all.append(qc)\n",
    "    \n",
    "probs = sampler.run(qc_all).result().quasi_dists\n",
    "\n",
    "prob1 = []\n",
    "for prob in probs:\n",
    "    if 1 in prob:\n",
    "        prob1.append(prob[1])\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        prob1.append(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "#qc_all[2].draw('mpl')"
   ]

    "prob1_phase = []\n",
    "qc_all = []\n",
    "for ang in angles:\n",
    "    qc = QuantumCircuit(2, 1)\n",
    "    qc.h(0)\n",
    "    qc.x(1)\n",
    "    qc.cp(ang, 0, 1)\n",
    "    qc.h(0)\n",
    "    qc.measure(0, 0)\n",
    "    qc_all.append(qc)\n",
    "\n",
    "probs = sampler.run(qc_all).result().quasi_dists\n",
    "\n",
    "for prob in probs:\n",
    "    if 1 in prob:\n",
    "        prob1_phase.append(prob[1])\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        prob1_phase.append(0)"

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Bernstein-Vazirani "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f54ec1f4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$f:\\{0, 1\\}^n \\rightarrow \\{0, 1\\}$ where \n",
    "$f(x) = x\\cdot a~(mod2)$ with $a \\in \\{0, 1\\}^n$\n",
    "\n",
    "Find $a$ where $n = 3$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "72c4d48a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def BV(U):\n",
    "    num_str = U.num_qubits - 1\n",
    "    qc = QuantumCircuit(num_str + 1, num_str)\n",
    "    qc.x(num_str)\n",
    "    qc.h(range(num_str + 1))\n",
    "    qc.barrier()\n",
    "    qc.append(U, range(num_str+1))\n",
    "    qc.barrier()\n",
    "    qc.h(range(num_str))\n",
    "    qc.measure(range(num_str), range(num_str))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return qc"
   ]
  },
